analysis: The agent used "Saturday" for the dayOfWeek parameter instead of "Sunday" as expected; it failed to infer the specific day required by the benchmark when "this weekend" was mentioned, resulting in a non-matching function call.
The agent included an unsupported parameter "radius" in its DR_OT function call, resulting in a mismatch with the expected function signature, which only accepts the "restaurantNames" parameter.

The agent used the correct function ("AI_I") with appropriate parameters but capitalized parameter values ("Millennials", "Fitness") instead of using lowercase ("millennials", "fitness"), leading to a mismatch with the expected output format.

The agent's function call included an extra "targetAudience" argument not present in the tool schema, causing a mismatch with the expected signature and resulting in the evaluator not recognizing the function call as valid.
The agent used "Winter" with an uppercase "W" instead of the required lowercase "winter" in the "seasonNames" parameter, leading to a mismatch with the expected function call arguments.

The model incorrectly included an unsupported "timeZone" parameter in its call to CAQI_D, while only "cityNames" is allowed. This caused the evaluator to reject the function call as no valid match was found.

The agent omitted required parameters ("apiKey" and "refreshRate") in its GAQ_C function call, resulting in a function signature mismatch with the expected call. These missing fields caused the evaluator to reject the function call despite correct intent.

The agent incorrectly included an unsupported "visitDuration" parameter in the DFP_R function call, causing a mismatch with the expected function signature that only accepts the "childrenAges" parameter.
The agent capitalized the sector name ("Technology") instead of using the expected lowercase ("technology"), resulting in a parameter mismatch and no matching function call being recognized.
